[SN]TITLE[SN]
Teenagers rescue pensioner from fire in Liverpool

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A pensioner from Liverpool has said she owes her life to three teenagers who rescued her from a house fire.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
30 September 2014 Last updated at 20:15 BST
Sylvia Flynn was watching television in her living room unaware that a chip pan fire had engulfed her kitchen.
But three 15 year-olds spotted the flames as they walked past.
Ellie, Elle and Kieran pulled Sylvia and her dog Rolo to safety and alerted the emergency services.
